<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?> <?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="rss.xsl"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"> <channel> <title>Apache Iceberg™</title><description>Blogs for Apache Iceberg</description><link>https://iceberg.apache.org/</link><atom:link href="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /> <language>en</language> <pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 07:10:15 -0000</pubDate> <lastBuildDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 07:10:15 -0000</lastBuildDate> <ttl>1440</ttl> <generator>MkDocs RSS plugin - v1.19.0</generator> <image> <url>https://iceberg.apache.org/assets/images/Iceberg-logo.svg</url> <title>Apache Iceberg™</title> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/</link> </image> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg C++ 0.3.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce the 0.3.0 release of Apache &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp&#34;&gt;Iceberg C++&lt;/a&gt;. This release includes &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp/compare/v0.2.0...v0.3.0&#34;&gt;over 140 pull requests&lt;/a&gt; from 23 contributors, including 11 first-time contributors.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iceberg-cpp&lt;/code&gt; is a native C++ implementation of the Apache Iceberg table format, providing libraries for reading, writing, and managing Iceberg tables in C++ applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.3.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.3.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg Go 0.6.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce version 0.6.0 of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-go&#34;&gt;iceberg-go&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This release covers approximately three months of development since the 0.5.0 release in March 2026 and is the result of merging nearly &lt;strong&gt;200 PRs&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;40 contributors&lt;/strong&gt;, including &lt;strong&gt;26 first-time contributors&lt;/strong&gt;. See the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-go/compare/v0.5.0...v0.6.0&#34;&gt;full changelog&lt;/a&gt; for the complete list of changes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iceberg-go&lt;/code&gt; is a native Go implementation of the Apache Iceberg table format, providing libraries for reading, writing, and managing Iceberg tables in Go applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-go-0.6.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-go-0.6.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg 1.11.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce the release of Apache Iceberg 1.11.0. This release is the result of over &lt;strong&gt;1,000 commits&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;200+ contributors&lt;/strong&gt;. See the &lt;a href=&#34;https://iceberg.apache.org/releases/#1110-release&#34;&gt;release notes&lt;/a&gt; for the complete list of changes.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-1.11.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-1.11.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg Rust 0.9.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce version 0.9.0 of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-rust&#34;&gt;iceberg-rust&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This release covers development work from early January through early March 2026 and is the result of merging &lt;strong&gt;109 PRs&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;28 contributors&lt;/strong&gt;, including &lt;strong&gt;8 new contributors&lt;/strong&gt;. See the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-rust/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#v090---2026-03-10&#34;&gt;changelog&lt;/a&gt; for the complete list of changes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iceberg-rust&lt;/code&gt; is a native Rust implementation of the Apache Iceberg specification, providing high-performance libraries for reading, writing, and managing Iceberg tables in Rust applications and through Python bindings (&lt;code&gt;pyiceberg-core&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-rust-0.9.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-rust-0.9.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg Go 0.5.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce version 0.5.0 of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-go&#34;&gt;iceberg-go&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This release covers approximately five months of development since the 0.4.0 release in October 2025 and is the result of merging over &lt;strong&gt;110 PRs&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;31 contributors&lt;/strong&gt;, including &lt;strong&gt;18 first-time contributors&lt;/strong&gt;. See the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-go/compare/v0.4.0...v0.5.0&#34;&gt;full changelog&lt;/a&gt; for the complete list of changes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iceberg-go&lt;/code&gt; is a native Go implementation of the Apache Iceberg table format, providing libraries for reading, writing, and managing Iceberg tables in Go applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-go-0.5.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-go-0.5.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Introducing the Apache Iceberg File Format API</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>announcement</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is excited to announce the finalization of the File Format API, a major architectural milestone that makes file formats &lt;strong&gt;pluggable&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;consistent&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;engine‑agnostic&lt;/strong&gt; across the Iceberg Java codebase.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-file-format-api/</link> <pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-file-format-api/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg Python 0.11.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce the 0.11.0 release of Apache &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-python&#34;&gt;Iceberg Python&lt;/a&gt;. This release includes over &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-python/compare/pyiceberg-0.10.0...pyiceberg-0.11.0&#34;&gt;380 pull requests&lt;/a&gt; from 50+ contributors, including 28 first-time contributors.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;These notes cover the highlights. For the full list, see the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-python/releases/tag/pyiceberg-0.11.0&#34;&gt;changelog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-python-0.11.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 10 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-python-0.11.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg Rust 0.8.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce version 0.8.0 of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-rust&#34;&gt;iceberg-rust&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This release covers development work from late November 2025 through early January 2026 and is the result of merging &lt;strong&gt;144 PRs&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;37 contributors&lt;/strong&gt;. See the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-rust/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#v080---2026-01-06&#34;&gt;changelog&lt;/a&gt; for the complete list of changes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iceberg-rust&lt;/code&gt; is a native Rust implementation of the Apache Iceberg specification, providing high-performance libraries for reading, writing, and managing Iceberg tables in Rust applications and through Python bindings (&lt;code&gt;pyiceberg-core&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-rust-0.8.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 02 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-rust-0.8.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Apache Iceberg C++ 0.2.0 Release</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>release</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce the 0.2.0 release of Apache Iceberg C++. This release includes &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp/compare/v0.1.0...v0.2.0&#34;&gt;over 200 merged pull requests&lt;/a&gt; from 23 distinct contributors.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The release notes below are not exhaustive and only expose selected highlights of the release. Many other bugfixes and improvements have been made: we refer you to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp/releases/tag/v0.2.0&#34;&gt;complete changelog&lt;/a&gt; for details.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.2.0-release/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 26 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.2.0-release/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Announcing Iceberg Summit 2026</title> <author>Apache Iceberg PMC</author> <category>announcement</category> <description>&lt;!-- - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more - contributor license agreements. See the NOTICE file distributed with - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership. - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0 - (the &#34;License&#34;); you may not use this file except in compliance with - the License. You may obtain a copy of the License at - - http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 - - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software - distributed under the License is distributed on an &#34;AS IS&#34; BASIS, - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and - limitations under the License. --&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iceberg Summit is officially coming back in 2026!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Mark your calendars! On &lt;strong&gt;April 8 and 9, 2026&lt;/strong&gt;, the Apache Iceberg community will gather once again in &lt;strong&gt;San Francisco&lt;/strong&gt; at the Marriott Marquis for two full days dedicated to all things Iceberg. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.icebergsummit.org/#register&#34;&gt;Register now&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to reserve your spot!&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/announcing-iceberg-summit-2026/</link> <pubDate>Sat, 10 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://iceberg.apache.org/rss.xml">Apache Iceberg™</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/announcing-iceberg-summit-2026/</guid> </item> </channel> </rss>